  animalID: Zara
  animalName: Zara
  species: Polar Bear
  scientificName: Ursus Maritimus
  status: 0
  biome: 3
  portrait: {fileID: -760466472361236605, guid: 9c53817347f35cd47bc826d725cde022, type: 3}
  journalArt: {fileID: 0}
  introDialogue: 'You are not afraid of me... interesting. Most of your kind would
    start running or gunning at the sight of me. You are different... interesting.
    There are people blocking the path to my hunting ground.

    They have drills.
    Equipment. Guns.


    I have not eaten in eleven days.


    I am not asking
    for help. I am simply telling you

    what is ahead. If you are going that way
    anyway.

'
  questDialogue: The Ice Golem was once a protector of these areas. He's now too
    angry to think straight. Put it to rest.
  completionDialogue: 'When I was three my mother showed me ice that

    stretched
    past the horizon. By the time I was five

    it was gone every summer.


    We
    adapt. That is what we do.


    But you cannot swim forever.'
  journalEntry: "Polar Bear | Ursus maritimus\r\nStatus: Vulnerable \u2014 26,000
    remain in the wild\r\n\r\nPolar bears depend entirely on sea ice to hunt seals.
    As Arctic ice retreats earlier each spring and forms later each autumn, bears
    are forced to fast for longer and longer periods.\r\n\r\nArctic sea ice has declined
    13% per decade since 1979. By 2100 it could disappear entirely in summer.\r\n\r\nPolar
    bears are also poisoned by industrial chemicals like PCBs which accumulate in
    their fatty tissue and damage their immune and reproductive systems.\r\n\r\nWhat
    you can do: Support Polar Bears International at polarbearsinternational.org\r\n"
  conservationFact: A single golden poison dart frog contains enough toxin to kill
    ten adult humans. Locals used it on blowgun darts for centuries,hence the name.
  doofNote: I once tried to synthesise dart frog toxin for a Paralyze-Inator. My
    lawyer has advised me not to discuss what happened next.
  questType: 1
